webcam video or simply record audio and their computer screen simultaneously  which allows adding sound to PowerPoint presentations and other course material EDIT All recorded captures can be modified in your dashboard and tailored for your lecture and student needs captures can be modified PUBLISH Captures created from both of these options can be linked to  Blackboard Learn and also accessed at Echo    org  Echo    ALP provides the instructor with reports on student activities such as viewing of Echoes and participation in discussions  and polling  Blackboard Learn HELP  present  and more Classroom Capture recordings must be scheduled ahead of time  and can be either one time events or repeating semester events  Captures are available within     hours of a one hour long lecture The ACCC assists with scheduling automatic capture of the east campus common use classrooms  For other classrooms  contact the appropriate department to have your lecture captured   east campus common use classrooms College of Pharmacy College of Medicine College of Dentistry Personal Capture is available to all UIC faculty and instructors by request  Please note you must already have your course created via Blackboard before submitting your request request course created via Blackboard For additional information  please consult the Echo Center Academic Staff Guide from the Echo System documentation page Academic Staff Guide There is no charge for this service LTS uic edu              Lecture Center E n t t tRoom E    Echo    System Administration Personal Capture Downloads ACCC Service Level Agreement  SLA Under   business days  unless in person training discussion is required  or escalation to the vendor is required Under   business days unless escalation to the vendor is required accc uic edu service status accc uic edu news all Provisional SLA   Currently under IT Governance review Provisional SLA   Currently under IT Governance review classroom recording lecture capture multimedia pers